item.dc:creator: @someone123456 someone123456
item.description:
@someone123456 wrote:

Double click little internet thing and choose preperties.

then Internet Protocal TCP/IP.

Click properties, Choose Use the following and put in

IP= 192.168.1.136
Subnet= just hit tab when on IP
Gateway = 192.168.1.1

Primary DNS 192.168.1.1
Secondary = Blank

Then go back to router and for IP put in 136 in that box. Happy?
